🧩 Step 3: Copy the Erlang Cookie

RabbitMQ nodes authenticate each other using a secret file called .erlang.cookie.
It must be identical on all nodes.

On rabbit1 (master):
sudo cat /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie


Copy that output (a long random string).

On rabbit2 (slave) and rabbit3(slave):
sudo systemctl stop rabbitmq-server
echo 'KYUFUQTAXDBFAUYCXGSWWEFUAHOU' | sudo tee /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie
sudo chown rabbitmq:rabbitmq /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie
sudo chmod 400 /var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie
sudo systemctl start rabbitmq-server
   
   
   
   
🧩 Step 4: Form the Cluster
On rabbit2 (slave) rabbit3 (slave):
sudo rabbitmqctl stop_app
sudo rabbitmqctl reset
sudo rabbitmqctl join_cluster rabbit@rabbit1
sudo rabbitmqctl start_app


sudo nano /etc/rabbitmq/rabbitmq.conf
Add these lines:

default_queue_type = quorum
queue_master_locator = random


cd /usr/local/bin
